                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Charleston</placeName>\n                                        <date>April 20/44</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Dear Friend</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Aware of your anxi=<lb/>=ety deep interest you\n                                        feel in our<lb/> cause the welfare continuation<lb/> of\n                                        Judaism I hasten to inform you<lb/> of the result of our law\n                                        suit, it<lb/> came on as <sic>apporated</sic> on\n                                                  <date>Monday</date><lb/> last continued before the\n                                        court until<lb/> last night, when I tell you that but<lb/>\n                                        one witness was examined you cannot<lb/> but wonder how it\n                                        should have so<lb/> occupied so much time, especially<lb/>\n                                        as the Judge ruled out the religious<lb/> questions, but\n                                        notwithstanding it was<lb/> incidentally introduced by our\n                                        counsel<lb/> the Examination of <persName>Mr.\n                                                  Valentine</persName> the<lb/> secretary occupied 2\n                                        days, our consul<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr. Memminger</persName> opened the case,\n                                        clearly<lb/> extensively did he go into the merits<lb/> not\n                                        only in the law but in the changes<lb/> alterations of our\n                                        sacred religion, but after<lb/> a patent hearing the judge\n                                        decided that<lb/> the religious charity or\n                                                  <sic>allecations</sic> could have<lb/> no bearing\n                                        on the case that it was altogether<lb/> a matter of Law,\n                                        upon that only could the<lb/> case stand, after the\n                                        examination of <persName>Mr. V</persName></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tm72s6b/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
