                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><persName>Mr. Baily</persName> the opposite counsel declined<lb/>\n                                        calling any counsel wherefore had<lb/> to abandon one of the\n                                        charges of which<lb/> had been brought collusion fraud<lb/>\n                                        by which means he secured the advantage<lb/> of the closing\n                                        speech – It is the only<lb/> consolation [?] our [?]<lb/>\n                                        left us to know that our <sic>counsellor</sic><lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr Memminger</persName> [?] acquitted [?]<lb/>\n                                        with more than the [?] with<lb/> which they have always been\n                                        distinguished<lb/> The formers gentleman closing\n                                        address<lb/> occupied 5 ½ hours – The charge of the<lb/> [?]\n                                        was short but lucid his [?]<lb/> conclusions were that the\n                                        Board of trus<lb/>tees were not allowed could not<lb/> meet\n                                        without the President that<lb/> no meeting could take place\n                                        without<lb/> the consent of the President -<lb/> Of course\n                                        such a charge from the<lb/> [?], if even the jury was any\n                                        ways<lb/> favourably disposed toward us, settled I<lb/> have\n                                        no doubt in their minds any<lb/> doubt or feelings in their\n                                        own <sic>judgement</sic><lb/> after [?] our but a little\n                                        time<lb/> brought in their verdict against us</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My feelings as well as my friends are of<lb/>\n                                        course [?] and to say the least, but<lb/> that is not the\n                                        worst, we all now at<lb/> sea again without a pilot, nay\n                                        without<lb/> a heaven to steer for, we are in a<lb/>\n                                        dreadful situation, we know not what<lb/> is but to do. I\n                                        truly regret that you</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tm72s6b/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
